While navigating through wiki pages, tickets, reviews, users can mark them as
favorites. Back end logic remembers it and pushes information in your way.
So abstractly speaking, favorites are tools that captures your wishes, using
it to filter useful information from an avalanche of digital content for you,
in real-time.

Users can even mark an entire project as their favorite. Favorites are one of
the many notification methods that we have built into Zeta. It is also
possible to mark wiki pages and tickets as favorites while viewing or editing
them in your editor.
